   Programs and Project
   white spacer for site Vital Habitat & Biological Resources
   Restoration of living resources and vital habitat is the highest
   priority of Chesapeake 2000. The CBP is developing plans to restore
   vital habitats and living resources including submerged aquatic
   vegetation and fisheries.

   collage of photographs representing habitat

   .

   [w_spacer.gif]   white image spacer Also, the Department of Interior is
   developing conservation measures to protect water birds in the Atlantic
   Flyway. To develop the strategies to conserve and restore the
   ecosystem, scientific information is needed to understand the complex
   relation of living resources and associated habitats to environmental
   factors in the Bay and its watershed. The USGS will focus on
   documenting the factors affecting the health of fish and water birds
   and their habitats.

   bullet Submerged Aquatic Vegetation
